<div id="subtree-container" class="subtree-container"><div class="aea2d7dde423afa7ad9351a0886150a8-scss b51b00c1669ad99a1c607cd1e77c2824-scss" style="inset: 437px 269px 0px 0px; justify-content: flex-end;"><div class="afeebf1df237d4103108ba40799802d6-scss"><div class="c13443431e58facf06f9d12490b92a82-scss" style="width: 90vw; max-width: 8.5in;"><div class="_0df5ec6b9902d7d22ccfa3ebb4f35211-scss">Pipes and Fittings - Calculation of Fittings Length</div><div class="e5e059a27f4c194020f0d961a3cb5989-scss" dir="auto"><div class="fr-view"><p id="isPasted">Measure the length of the pipes added to the length of the fittings, in meters, as illustrated in Figure 12.&nbsp;</p>
<p>This measurement methodology results in a more accurate estimate of the total network length compared to ratio methodology, considering that the length of the fittings is directly obtained from the models.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Independently of the employed authoring tool, the length of the fittings must be reported through a parameter that calculates it based on the specific dimensions of each element.&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="https://private.lodplanner.com/projects/11696/plan-content/1700590052462_87e4ff70-55b3-4e76-bd1a-3945157bb084.png?Expires=1768815902&amp;Signature=Si-UKVk7qMS5fIvrIMVCz2LedTrU~LZQD7ER8DQk9nwz-IQBU9XMs~FLNJ9O0cHXKTmx5cHqlWTOUSBwg3BltSWrO4vFyYGUrKl5xS7QZywUf~iBattxNWgHAFylj718V-UcqykDmM-8Y3gLd6Oer9Xq3UTST-QZ3Y28bHCZRCjf1NGvsjvzjx7zP48xF7-wtAa1UJDHU9VvTo9vfPFETSJ7JsxUx5dIxmNAnQAUpRTMMYW6DI6MVxTghTWxF7kFzhNDWenRLuvumZblIOP3q86uWfld78Nf3J7y8aoni9J0~9vkqDHxnKq3Y-vZqMiQuwQ-m7uj4mSxCJ~iT5NElw__&amp;Key-Pair-Id=APKAJRIVA6WNZT4BZJPQ" class="fr-fic fr-dii" style="width: 614px;"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Figure 12 - Fittings Length Method.&nbsp;</em></p>
<p>As a result, this technique is applied during the estimate and design project phases.&nbsp;</p>
<p>However, it is crucial to consider the inherent risks associated with this approach, particularly when the design demands fittings with big dimensions or special features, as it may have implications on cost estimation.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>